Definition.WordDefinition:
Manhood \Man"hood\, n. [Man- + -hood.] 1. The state of being man as a human being, or man as distinguished from a child or a woman. [1913 Webster]
2. Manly quality; virility; courage; bravery; resolution. [1913 Webster]
I am ashamed That thou hast power to shake my manhood thus. --Shak. [1913 Webster]
3. The genitalia of a male human. [PJC]
4. The condition of being a human being. [PJC]
manhood n 1: the state of being a man; manly qualities 2: the quality of being human; "he feared the speedy decline of all manhood" [syn: {humanness}, {humanity}] 3: the status of being a man
